newsitem.title: SWEDEN: Riksbank meeting ends, no rate changes announced.
newsitem.headline: Riksbank meeting ends, no rate changes announced.

text.p: Sweden's Riksbank (central bank) ended on Thursday its bi-weekly board meeting without announcing any changes to its key interest rates.

The Riksbank's deposit and lending rates are currently set at 4.75 percent and 6.25 respectively, and the repo rate, which is the central element of the three-tiered interest rate system, was lowered by 10 basis points to 5.05 percent on Tuesday.
